When implementing code, generating functions, writing tests, or creating 
new files, use the ollama ask_model tool with model qwen3-coder-next 
to generate the code.

Use your own reasoning for:
- Architecture decisions and planning
- Code review and quality assessment  
- Breaking down complex tasks into steps
- Deciding what files to create or modify

Delegate to qwen3-coder-next for:
- Writing the actual code implementations
- Generating boilerplate and templates
- Writing test cases
- Creating Frappe doctypes, controllers, and client scripts


